cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on image understanding and scene graph generation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques and modeling inter-dependency among objects, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with generating structured descriptions of images. Finally, the paper uses the Visual Genome benchmark, which is a dataset for multimedia (cs.MM) research.
